Date: Thu, 8 Jan 2015 23:17:12 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 368/451] spi: fsl-dspi: bug fix dspi incorrect CS de-assert

Spi chip select signal need to keep asserted between several spi_transfer
in one same spi_message. But the driver will de-assert CS signal between serval spi_transfer
in one same spi_message under some condiations.This patch fix this bug.

Signed-off-by: Haikun Wang <b53464@freescale.com>
Change-Id: I28153974553bcbc96d378ea6beee4e143ad15272
Reviewed-on: http://git.am.freescale.net:8181/34984
Tested-by: Review Code-CDREVIEW <CDREVIEW@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Stuart Yoder <stuart.yoder@freescale.com>
[Xulin: Original patch taken from
Linux-LS1043A-SDK-V0.4-SOURCE-20150826-yocto.iso]
Signed-off-by: Xulin Sun <xulin.sun@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/spi/spi-fsl-dspi.c |    4 ++--
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/spi/spi-fsl-dspi.c b/drivers/spi/spi-fsl-dspi.c
index bc77771..b736558 100644
--- a/drivers/spi/spi-fsl-dspi.c
+++ b/drivers/spi/spi-fsl-dspi.c
@@ -338,10 +338,10 @@ static int dspi_transfer_one_message(struct spi_master *master,
 		dspi->cur_msg = message;
 		dspi->cur_chip = spi_get_ctldata(spi);
 		dspi->cs = spi->chip_select;
+		dspi->cs_change = 0;
 		if (dspi->cur_transfer->transfer_list.next
 				== &dspi->cur_msg->transfers)
-			transfer->cs_change = 1;
-		dspi->cs_change = transfer->cs_change;
+			dspi->cs_change = 1;
 		dspi->void_write_data = dspi->cur_chip->void_write_data;
 
 		dspi->dataflags = 0;
